        "image": "assets/uploads/articles/Hino_Promo_Service_Banjir_headlines.jpg",
        "description": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><b>Jakarta, 6 Januari 2020</b> –&nbsp; Pada penutupan tahun 2019 disaat menyambut tahun baru 2020, beberapa kawasan diguyur hujan yang cukup tinggi. Intensitas hujan yang lebat ini menyebabkan beberapa kawasan seperti Jabotabek dan kota – kota lainnya mengalami banjir besar yang mengakibatkan rumah – rumah terendam dan warga pun harus di evakuasi keluar dari area tersebut. Banjir tidak hanya menerjang area pemukiman warga, beberapa kawasan industri atau bisnis turut juga terkena banjir besar diawal tahun ini yang mengakibatkan banyak kendaraan komersial untuk armada bisnis konsumen turut terendam dan membuat kegiatan bisnis mereka terganggu.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sebagai bentuk Total Support kepada para pelanggan dan membantu bisnis mereka pulih seperti sedia kala. Hino memberikan program spesial bagi konsumen yang terdampak atas bencana banjir tersebut, PT Hino Motors Sales Indonesia (HMSI), selaku main distributor resmi kendaraan truk dan bus Hino di Indonesia memberikan program spesial berupa “<b>Hino Service Campaign Peduli Banjir</b>” bagi konsumen yang kendaraannya terdampak banjir. Program <i>Service campaign</i> ini untuk semua tipe kendaraan Hino yang khusus mengalami kerusakan akibat banjir. Penawaran spesial yang diberikan berupa <b>diskon suku cadang hingga 45%</b> serta tambahan <b>diskon untuk jasa servis sebanyak 10%</b>. Program berlaku <b>di seluruh dealer resmi Hino yang ada di Indonesia</b> dan berlangsung mulai dari tanggal <b>6 Januari 2020 sampai 31 Maret 2020</b> meliputi pekerjaan ringan seperti pergantian; kanvas rem, filter oli, filter solar, filer udara, oli mesin, oli transmisi, dan oli differential, serta untuk greasing bearing roda. Pekerjaan medium berupa perbaikan sistem rem (master rem, brake chamber), perbaikan sistem kemudi dan kaki – kaki<i> (kingpin, tie rod)</i>. Serta pekerjaan berat yaitu <i>overhaul </i>mesin, <i>overhaul </i>transmisi, <i>overhaul differential.</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hino turut juga memberikan gratis bagi para konsumen yang kendaraannya terkena dampak banjir besar berupa <b>gratis pengecekan</b> 55 item yang terdampak seperti mesin, transmisi, propeller shaft, garden, system hydraulik, sistem rem &amp; roda,sistem kemudi,sistem suspensi,sistem kelistirkan dan bodi kendaraan. Untuk itu diharapkan konsumen dapat terbantu dengan Hino Service Campaign Peduli Banjir ini sehingga konsumen terbantu dalam menjalankan bisnis nya, untuk informasi lanjut konsumen dapat mendatangi <b>dealer – dealer Hino terdekat yang ada di seluruh Indonesia </b>atau menghubungi Hino customer call center di nomer 0 800 100 4466.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><i>“Kami berharap banjir ini tidak memberikan dampak yang signifikan bagi kegiatan bisnis pelanggan, namun sebagai wujud Total Support kami kepada customer, kami harapkan konsumen dapat terbantu dengan program ini dan mereka dapat memanfaatkannya di seluruh dealer Hino yang ada di Indonesia”. </i>Tutup <b>Irwan Supriyono,Senior Executive Officer After Sales HMSI.</b></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><b><br></b><img src=\"https://www.hino.co.id/assets/uploads/articles/ec8956637a99787bd197eacd77acce5e.jpg\" style=\"width: 830.873px; height: 1173.51px;\"></p><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></div>",
        "description_english": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><b>Jakarta, January 6, 2020</b> - At the close of 2019 while welcoming the new year 2020, some regions were hit by quite high rainfall. The intensity of heavy rains caused several areas such as Jabotabek and other cities to experience severe flooding which resulted in houses being flooded and residents had to be evacuated out of the area. Flooding not only hit residential areas, several industrial or business areas were also affected by major flooding at the beginning of this year which resulted in many commercial vehicles for the consumer business fleet being submerged and disrupting their business activities.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As a form of Total Support to customers and help their business recover as before. Hino provides a special program for consumers affected by the flood disaster, PT Hino Motors Sales Indonesia (HMSI), as the official main distributor of Hino trucks and buses in Indonesia, provides a special program in the form of a \"Hino Service Campaign for Flood Care\" for consumers whose vehicles are affected by flooding . This Service campaign program is for all types of Hino vehicles specifically damaged by flooding. Special offers are given in the form of spare parts discounts of up to 45% and additional discounts for services as much as 10%. The program applies to all authorized Hino dealers in Indonesia and runs from 6 January 2020 to 31 March 2020 including light work such as replacements; brake canvas, oil filter, solar filter, air filter, engine oil, transmission oil and differential oil, as well as for wheel bearing greasing. Medium work includes repairing the brake system (master brake, brake chamber), repairing the steering system and legs (kingpin, tie rod). And heavy work, namely engine overhaul, transmission overhaul, overhaul differential.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hino also provides free for consumers whose vehicles are affected by major flooding in the form of free checking of 55 affected items such as engines, transmissions, propeller shafts, gardens, hydraulic systems, brake &amp; wheel systems, steering systems, suspension systems, electrical systems and vehicle bodies . For this reason, consumers are expected to be helped by the Hino Service Campaign for Flood Care so that consumers can be helped in running their business. For further information, consumers can go to the nearest Hino dealers in Indonesia or contact the Hino customer call center at number 0 800 100 4466.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\"We hope that this flood does not have a significant impact on customers' business activities, but as a form of our Total Support to customers, we hope consumers can be helped by this program and they can utilize it in all Hino dealers in Indonesia\". Close Irwan Supriyono, HMSI Senior Sales After Sales Officer.</p>",
