        "title": "Pabrik Hino di Indonesia Sementara Stop Produksi",
        "title_english": "Hino Plant Stops Temporary Production Again",
        "sub_title": null,
        "image": "assets/uploads/articles/Perakitan_Sasis_Truk_Hino_di_Pabrik_Purwakarta.jpg",
        "description": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Purwakarta – 8\r\nMei 2020. Badan Pusat Statistik (BPS) menyebutkan pertumbuhan ekonomi Indonesia\r\npada kuartal I 2020 sebesar 2,97%. Jauh turun bila dibandingkan dengan\r\npertumbuhan perekonomian di sepanjang 2019 yang masih diatas 5%. Pandemi\r\nCOVID-19 berdampak juga pada pasar kendaraan niaga di Indonesia. <o:p></o:p></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">PT Hino Motors\r\nManufacturing Indonesia (HMMI), per hari ini (Jumat, 8 Mei 2020) melakukan\r\npenghentian sementara kegiatan produksi. Periode stop produksi terhitung sejak\r\ntanggal 8 Mei 2020 sampai dengan 5 Juni 2020.<o:p></o:p></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Presiden\r\nDirektur HMMI, Masahiro Aso mengatakan “kami ingin bisa melalui kondisi sulit\r\nsaat ini bersama – sama dengan semua pemangku kepentingan. Kami akan terus\r\nmendukung program pemerintah dan berkontribusi untuk percepatan pemulihan\r\nkondisi perekonomian nasional”<o:p></o:p></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Produksi dan\r\nStok Prioritas di Tipe Unggulan<o:p></o:p></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Meski demikian,\r\nuntuk memenuhi permintaan pasar, stok kendaran Hino tetap aman untuk memenuhi\r\npermintaan dari konsumen. Karena produksi sudah disesuaikan dengan tingkat\r\nkebutuhan dan sesuai prioritas tipe produk yang banyak diminta oleh konsumen.\r\nSelain itu dealer Hino tetap beroperasi baik itu penjualan, bengkel perawatan\r\nmaupun suku cadang. Untuk memberikan rasa tenang bagi konsumen dan karyawan,\r\nseluruh kegiatan operasional tersebut dipantau dengan ketat dan memenuhi\r\nregulasi pemerintah mengenai penerapan physical distancing.<o:p></o:p></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Selain itu untuk\r\nmempermudah roda bisnis konsumen setianya, Hino juga masih terus memberikan\r\nprogram – program layanan purna jual yang lebih ekonomis dimasa pandemic COVID-\r\n19 ini. Program tersebut antara lain, servis berkala kelipatan 10K, extra\r\ndiskon sampai dengan 37% untuk Aki HMSI Original Part (HOP), gratis pengecekan,\r\ngratis filter oli, gratis jasa servis ganti oli. gratis layanan Home Service.\r\nAda juga program Servis Hemat Mobil Terawat, untuk perbaikan dan over haul\r\ndiskon hingga 45% untuk suku cadang dan diskon 20% jasa servis. Selain promo\r\nservis berkala, Hino juga memberikan promo potongan harga untuk Strainer Kit\r\nmenjadi hanya 900.000 ribu. Strainer ini berfungsi untuk memperpanjang filter\r\nkendaraan dengan pengunaan bahan bakar B30<o:p></o:p></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Informasi lebih\r\nlanjut dapat dilihat di www.hino.co.id atau menghubungi Hino Customer Care\r\nCenter via telp 0 800 100 4444 atau WhatsApp 0815 1900 1900 yang bisa dihubungi\r\nselama 24 jam setiap hari melalui telepon bebas pulsa.</font><o:p></o:p></p>",
        "description_english": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><strong><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Purwakarta – 8 May 2020. The Central Statistics\r\nAgency (BPS) said Indonesia's economic growth in the first quarter of 2020 was\r\n2.97%. Big decreased when compared with economic growth throughout 2019 which\r\nis still above 5%. This is also reflected in commercial vehicle market in\r\nIndonesia.<o:p></o:p></font></span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">PT Hino Motors Manufacturing\r\nIndonesia (HMMI), as per today (Friday, May 8<sup>th</sup> 2020) will temporary\r\nstop all production activities. The stop production period implemented from May\r\n8<sup>th</sup>, 2020 until June 5<sup>th</sup>, 2020. <o:p></o:p></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">President Director HMMI,\r\nMasahiro Aso said “We would like to overcome this difficult condition with all\r\nof our stakeholder. We will keep continue supporting to the government program\r\nand contribute to the speedy recovery of national economic condition.<o:p></o:p></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n6.0pt;margin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Production and Priority Stock by Favored\r\nType<o:p></o:p></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">However, to fulfill market\r\ndemand, Hino vehicle stock remains stay safe to meet customer demand. Because\r\nproduction has been adjusted to the level of needs and according to priority\r\ntypes of products that are much demanded by customer. In addition, Hino dealers\r\ncontinue to operate either for sales, maintenance workshops and spare parts. To\r\nprovide comfort for customer and employees, all operational activities are\r\nclosely monitored and comply with government regulations regarding implementation\r\nof physical distancing.<o:p></o:p></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">In addition to simplifying wheels\r\nof its loyal consumer business, Hino also continues to provide more economical\r\nafter-sales service programs during COVID-19 pandemic. These programs include\r\nperiodic service multiples of 10K, extra discounts up to 37% for HMSI Original\r\nPart (HOP) batteries, free checking, free oil filters, free oil change service.\r\nfree Home Service. There is also a Car Maintenance Services program, for repairs\r\nand over hauls up to 45% discount on spare parts and 20% discount se for service.\r\nIn addition periodic service promo, Hino also provides promo discounts for Strainer\r\nKits only 900,000 thousand. This strainer serves to extend the vehicle filter\r\nby using B30 fuel. <o:p></o:p></font></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><span lang=\"EN-ID\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Further information can be seen at www.hino.co.id or contacting Hino\r\nCustomer Care Center via phone 0 800 100 4444 or WhatsApp 0815 1900 1900 which\r\ncan be contacted 24 hours a day via toll free.</font><o:p></o:p></span></p>",
